('239898', 'PEDIATRIC STRIP CROWNS', 'Dental', 'Pedodontics', 'Crowns', 5.3, '<ol>\r\n<li>Pediatric Strip Crowns are transparent plastic crown forms used for restoring primary anterior and posterior teeth.\r\n<li>Advancements in composite materials have made Strip Crowns more durable while reaming the most esthetic\r\nrestoration for primary teeth.\r\n<li>Strip Crowns are an easy chair side procedure and final restorations are more compatible with gum tissue than\r\nstainless steel crowns.\r\n<li>Anterior Strip Crowns are comparable in size to 3MTM crown forms. Available in sizes 1-4 upper left and right\r\ncentrals and laterals.\r\n<li>Upper and lower cuspids are also available in sizes 1-6.\r\nPosterior Strip Crowns are comparable in size to 3MTM Unitek stainless steel crowns.\r\n<li>Available in sizes 1-6 for upper and lower, left and right, 1st and 2nd molars.\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><b>Benefits :</b></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Thin interproximal walls allow for multiple restorations.\r\n<li>Perfect for repairing chipped corners and edges.\r\n<li>Parallel interproximal walls provide good contacts.\r\n<li>Plastic strips off easily leaving a smooth polished surface.\r\n<li>Available in a variety of sizes.\r\n<li>Easy to control shade with light cure composites.\r\n<li>Natural anatomy.\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'images/products/Dental/Pedodontics/239898.png', '', '2014-07-18 08:14:49'),
('249511', 'RETRACTING MICROTOME', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Microtomes', 7.1, '<p>\r\nRETRACTING MICROTOME : Originally designed for Cryostat Use in\r\nsub zero temperatures. Its smooth & balanced driving mechanism enables 1 micron sections to be in\r\ncut with ease, and the robust feed system delivers virtually flat uniform sections consistently.<br /><br />\r\n<b>SPECIFICATIONS: </b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Section Thickness : 1~20 microns in 1 micron steps   \r\n<li>Specimen Size : 40 x 55 mm\r\n<li>Knife Size : 36 mm wide, 120 mm Long\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nSupplied complete as above with a razor 120 mm with back & handle, object holders, dust "j\r\ncoven honing stone and oil can in cardboard box.\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/249511.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:24:24'),
