('605957', 'TISSUE PROCESSING - EMBEDDING', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Storage-Units', 7.3, '<h4>Cassette with Cover</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nCassettes keep specimen safely submerged in\r\nliquid. Efficient flow-through slots. Snap-latch and hinge-lock design\r\nprevent earlyseparation of base and lid and allows for one\r\nhand operation. Large labeling area on two\r\nsides of cassette. Anterior writing area is at\r\n35° angle\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Tissue Processing / Embedding Cassette without Cover\r\nmade of acetal polymer</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nCassettes keep specimen safely submerged in liquid. Efficient flowthrough\r\nslots. Snap-latch and hinge-lock design prevent early\r\nseparation of base and lid and allows for one hand operation. Large\r\nlabeling area on two sides of cassette. Anterior writing area is at 35°\r\nangle\r\n</p>\r\n<h4>Tissue Processing / Embedding Cassette with S.S Cover\r\nmade of acetal polymer</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nCassettes keep specimen safely submerged in liquid. Efficient flowthrough\r\nslots. Snap-latch and hinge-lock design prevent early\r\nseparation of base and lid and allows for one hand operation.\r\nLarge labeling area on two sides of cassette. Anterior writing area\r\nis at 35° angle\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/605957.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:34:58'),
('608551', 'PRESSURE SENSITIVE PROBE', 'Dental', 'Periodontics', 'Speciality-Instruments', 2.2, '<p>AXE pressure sensitive probe is used because of lack of standardised measuring force, clinical measurement obtained by various method of probing are subject to contradictory interpretation\r\nit is the only way to attain an objective assessment of periodontal conditions is by using force sensitive periodontal probe.\r\nWhen evaluating periodontal diseases probing measurements are affected by numerous subjective and instrument relatedinfluences\r\nIn the process actual probing depths are frequently underestimated. If the probing force is too low then the soft tissue morphology is more of the limiting factor for the probing measurement than is the share of coronal supra -alveolar fibre structures.AXE probes it is possible ,thanks to defined pressure of 0.2N to perform standardised probing measurements.\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Periodontics/608551.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:07:08'),
