('7019', 'Scalpel Handles List', 'Dental', 'Dental Instruments', 'Scalpel Handles', 0, '<tr><td>185/3</td><td>	Scalpel Handle No.3</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>185/5</td><td>	Skalpel Handle round straight </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>185/6</td><td>	Skalpel Handle round angled </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>185/7</td><td>	Blade Holder 360Â° rotating</td></tr>', 'images/products/Dental/Dental-Instruments/7019.png', 'images/products/Dental/Dental-Instruments/thumbs/7019.png', '2013-12-02 10:10:16'),
('707580', 'REVERSIBLE APRON', 'Medical', 'X-Ray Apron', '', 0, '<ol><li><b> Reversible Apron</b> provides two different colours to facilitate wearing both sides according to your mood and environment.\r\n<li>Available with/without attached thyroid collar.</ol>', 'images/products/Medical/X-Ray-Apron/707580.png', '', '2013-12-02 08:20:28'),
('708435', 'HYDRO SOLDERING MACHINE', 'Dental', 'Orthodontics', 'Equipments', 3.1, '<h4>HYDRO SOLDERING MACHINE (IMPORTED)</h4>\r\n<p>This industrial-strength machine converts Water into oxy-hydrogen fuel for\r\n an extremely hot and precise reducing flame operating at 4850*F.  \r\nThis machine is perfect for soldering and brazing in the orthodontic \r\nlaboratory environment.  110V/60hZ\r\nMade in the USA! </p>\r\n<h4>HYDRO SOLDERING MACHINE (INDIAN MADE)</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Hydrogen Soldering Units Solutions:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nConventional gas torches use butane or cooking gas which causes carbon deposition in soldering joint deteriorating the quality of the joint.  In hydro soldering units hydrogen and oxygen gas are generated through electrolysis of water on burning. It produces perfectly neutral and non oxygenizing flame for soldering and exasperates no residues. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Product Description:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThe Dentex Hydro solder is specially designed to enable the user to perform an easy operation with a high degree of accuracy and simplicity.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Technical data: </b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Mains voltage : 1x 230 V\r\n<li>Mains frequency : 50/60 Hz\r\n<li>Mains fuse : 1 x 10 A\r\n<li>Max. gas production : 60 litre.\r\n<li>Max. nozzle size : 0.7 mm\r\n<li>Dimensions W x H x D (mm) : 350 x 230 x 320\r\n<li>Weight : 16 kg\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nHydrogen Soldering Auto Machine (Mod no.) DHS-115.  Gas controlling torch, Rubber pipe, 10 Nozzle, Set marble welding pad,\r\nPressure gauge, Metal torch, stand lighter.\r\nMains connection voltage 230 volts 50HZ. \r\n</p>\r\n', 'images/products/Dental/Orthodontics/708435.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:19:45'),
('713500', 'FILM MARKER PEN', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'Consumables', 1.6, '<p>White ink, non erasable</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/713500.png', '', '2014-07-18 03:23:35'),
('717193', 'FULLY AUTOMATIC MICROTOME', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Microtomes', 7.1, '<p>\r\nFULLY AUTOMATIC MICROTOME Incorporates a combination of\r\nmotorized hand wheel movement and high precision motorized specimen feed, for high\r\nthroughput histology labs. Powerful sectioning motor enable us to cut even the hard specimen \r\neasily. The smartly located feature touch key enables us to control the operation easily. Apart from \r\nother safety feature it also has an emergency stop button. <br /><br />\r\n<b>Technical Specifications: </b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Section thickness Setting range : 0.5pm-100 pm \r\n<li>Trimming thickness setting range : 1pm-600pm\r\n<li>Setting values : 0.5pm-5pm increment step 0.5pm, 5pm-20um increment step 1 um, 20pm-60pm increment step 5 pm, 60pm-100pm increment step 10 pm\r\n<li>Minimum setting value : 0.5 pm\r\n<li>Sectioning Speed : AdjustabIe\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nComplete as above and supplied with sample pack of disposable blades.\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/717193.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:39:47'),
('722076', 'FACE BOW TRANSFER', 'Dental', 'Orthodontics', 'Articulators-and-Accessories', 3.2, '<p><b>CORI FACE BOW</b> is designed to figure out the occlusion relation with easy and accuracy. One touch screw of universal joint is perfect for transfer with simple and accuracy.<p>\r\n<ol><li><b>System</b><br />It is designed ergonomically so that the relationship of occlusion can be figured out easily.\r\n<li><b>Precision</b><br />The joints of Bite fork can be fixed with One touch screw at once, and it can be moved left, right and center\r\n<li><b>Operation</b><br />Convenient operation by the simple desgined structure.</ol>\r\n<a href="images/descriptions/955780.png" data-toggle="lightbox"><img class="img-responsive" src="images/descriptions/955780.png" /></a>\r\n\r\n', 'images/products/Dental/Orthodontics/722076.png', '', '2014-07-18 14:15:13'),
('722900', 'DENTAL X-RAY TRAINER', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'Equipments', 1.2, '<p>\r\nX-Ray simulator for practicing dental radiography use.\r\nJaw model allows the mastering of bisecting techniques.\r\nJaw model is X-Ray compatible.\r\nAcquire basic X-Ray techniques such as film angle and\r\nprojection angle for each area.\r\nFree-moving finger arm allows you to hold the film at the\r\nposition of your choice so you can practice 10 or 14\r\nexposure techniques.\r\nPhantom unit is stored inside the suitcase.\r\nCan be set up on the chair or on its own easily.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>DXTTR III is the advanced dental x-ray trainer developed\r\nfrom the original trainer created under the sponsorship of\r\nthe Bureau of Radiological Health of the Food and Drug\r\nAdministration for the purpose of illustrating proper\r\nradiographic positioning. The most realistic substitute\r\npatient available, it allows unlimited, consistent\r\ninstruction of all types of intraoral radiography, without\r\nconcern for patient radiation burden.</p>\r\n<ol><li>Eliminates patient variables, making it easier to\r\nevaluate student technique.\r\n<li>High repeatability makes possible series of radiographs,\r\nvarying exposure factors to demonstrate how they\r\ninfluence results. Comparisons can be made of various\r\nfilm placements and projections.\r\n<li>Plastic skull DXTTRs use a special plastic that emulates\r\nthe radiographic characteristics of natural materials.\r\nIdeal for teaching positioning.\r\n<li>Human skull DXTTRs, as available, are ideal for\r\nteaching positioning and radiographic interpretation.\r\nHuman skull DXTTRs follow all industry standards.\r\nEach head has its own unique characteristics. \r\n<li>Mechanical operations and components are designed\r\nfor durability, ease of use and life-like movements, \r\nwith a full selection of adjustment features.\r\n<li>An optional telescoping arm with spring-mounted, \r\nball-ended finger securely holds film packets during\r\nexposures.</ol>\r\n<p>It also provides a refurbishment service \r\nto keep your DXTTR in the best of health.<br /><br /><b>Construction</b><ol><li>Standard plastic skull DXTTR III is made of a special plastic that\r\nemulates the radiographic characteristics of natural materials. \r\n<li>Human skull DXTTRs are filled with tissue-equivalent material \r\nfor appropriate radio-absorption. \r\n<li>Teeth are firmly anchored by slightly resilient plastic gums that \r\nalso reduce chipping.\r\n<li>All teeth are coated with radiolucent, shock-absorbing material\r\nto minimize breakage.\r\n<li>The outer skin is tough and durable vinyl; the flesh is molded in\r\npolyurethane foam directly onto the skull. \r\n<li>Life-like, pliable tongue is supported on the floor of the mouth \r\nby a tissue-equivalent vinyl section, bonded to the base of the\r\nmandible.\r\n<li>Mandibles are articulated mechanically for smooth and durable\r\nmouth action. Machined nylon side plates are bonded firmly to \r\nthe rami.\r\n<li>The lever-and-ratchet mechanism is hardened steel for wear\r\nresistance and strength. The frame is constructed of welded \r\nsteel tubing. Other parts not subject to high stress are aluminum.\r\nAll parts are plated or otherwise finished to prevent rust and\r\ncorrosion.</ol>\r\n<p><b>Adjustment of Head, Arm and Finger</b></p>\r\n<ol><li>The head is mounted with a ball-and-socket joint corresponding \r\nto the base of the cervical spine, held securely in position by a\r\nclamping lever. The central supporting tube rotates forward and\r\nback in the frame to assist in positioning, with stops to prevent it\r\nfrom falling forward.\r\n<li>The optional arm assembly is mounted to the frame by a \r\nball-and-socket joint with its own clamping lever. The arm has a\r\nrotating telescoping section, on which the spring-loaded finger,\r\nwith an additional pivot, is mounted for wrist-like action.</ol>\r\n<p><b>REFURBISHMENT</b><br /><br />\r\nRefurbishment  is recommended every 12 months. \r\nStandard refurbishment consists of the following:</p>\r\n<ol><li>Replace vinyl head skin\r\n<li>Replace plastic foam flesh (if required)\r\n<li>Replace molded vinyl tongue\r\n<li>Replace molded vinyl neck-base\r\n<li>Replace finger ball and straighten finger (if required)\r\n<li>Replace head strap\r\n<li>Mechanical damage not listed above will be quoted separately. \r\n<li>Broken or missing teeth can be replaced at a nominal cost. There is \r\na 90-day warranty on parts and labor. </ol>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/722900.png', '', '2014-07-17 13:05:53'),
('731018', 'LINEAR TISSUE PROCESSORS', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Equipments', 7.4, '<p>\r\nLINEAR TISSUE PROCESSOR WITH TOUCH SCREEN: Linear Tissue Processor is an enclosed compact bench top unit. It has a user friendly\r\nsoftware. The lowering and lifting of a tissue basket is smooth and noiseless. All the reagents are\r\ncovered when not in use to minimize loss due to evaporation. Illumination of the working chamber\r\nenables clear view of the process. An exhaust fan is provided to dispose of reagent vapors away\r\nfrom the laboratory.<br /><br />\r\n<b>Technical Specification: </b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>No of Stations : 12 \r\n<li>Reagent jar Capacity : 1000mI\r\n<li>Paraffin Station : 3\r\n<li>Programmable :Yes, upto 15 programmes\r\n<li>Battery Backup : Yes\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nMTP-L-1 12: Technically same as MTP-L-111 but supplied with 2 Its. capacity\r\ninstead of 1 Its.\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/731018.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:48:39'),
('732452', 'Osteotomy and Tracheotomy Kit List 1', 'Dental', 'Oral Surgery', 'Osteotomy and Tracheotomy Kits', 0, '<thead><tr><th>Osteotomy kitï¿½</th></tr></thead>\r\n<tr><td>Periosteal Elevator Fibre Handed - No. 5</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Bone Cutting Forceps - Double Action Curved 5ï¿½ï¿½</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Bone Nibbler - Double Action Curved 5ï¿½ï¿½</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Tessier Osteotomes Straight - 5,10,15mm</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Tessier Osteotome Curved - 10mm</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Fine Osteotomes Straight - 4,6,8mm</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Fine Osteotomes Curved - 6mm</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Fine Chisels Straight 6mm</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Nylon Faced Hammer - Medium</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Calipers Castroviejo</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Bone Trephine - Medium</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Cartilage Crusher - Rectangular Shape</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Pterigoidous Chisel - 10mm</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Aluminium General Box - Anodized Medium</td></tr>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Surgery/732452.png', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Surgery/thumbs/732452.png', '2014-07-19 03:33:11'),
('739471', 'SEMI AUTOMATIC CRYOSTAT MICROTOME', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Microtomes', 7.1, '<p>\r\nSEMI AUTOMATIC CRYOSTAT MICROTOME: The cryostat is `    \r\nergonomically designed keeping in view user needs and safety. It incorporates an optimized    \r\ncooling system (double compressor) with rapid specimen freezing and smooth precise \r\norientation for high quality sectioning in histology, pro-environment refrigerant, a rapid \r\nrefrigeration mode, a peltier unit, and a LCD Screen which displays data such as sample \r\ntravel, section thickness and temperature. It can be easily programmed for both start and \r\nstop. Easy to operate control panel with controls for temperature and time. UV is used for  \r\ndisinfection. Equipped with a closed drainage system that ensures collection of condensed\r\nand defrost fluids in a container<br /><br />\r\n<b>Salient Features:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Specimen retraction function protects the specimen from blade injury\r\n<li>Trimming/Sectioning button makes it easy to switch to the desired mode\r\n<li>Rapid Refrigeration Mode allows desired temperature drop in 60mins\r\n<li>Working area is easy to clean and disinfect\r\n<li>Eas to read LCD screen\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Technical Specifications:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Section Thickness Range : 1um-60um, 1pm-10um, in 1um increment, 10pm-20um, in 2pm increments, 20pm-60um, in 5pm increments\r\n<li>Trimming Range : 10pm-300pm in 10pm increments\r\n<li>Specimen Retraction : 5-75um in 5pm increments \r\n<li>Lowest Temp. of Peltier Unit : -50°c\r\n<li>Cooling Downtime to -30°c : 60 mins\r\n<li>Maximum Specimen Size : 35mm x 35mm\r\n<li>Specimen Vertical Stroke : 65mm\r\n<li>Specimen Horizontal Feed : 25mm\r\n</ol>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/739471.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:27:18'),
('740081', 'LEAD GLOVES', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'X-Ray-Protective-Apparels', 1.8, '<ol><li>Easy to wear \r\n<li>Light weight</li> \r\n<li>Comfortable to use for longer hours</li>\r\n<li>Prevents sweating </li>\r\n<li>Does’nt hurt fingers</li>\r\n<li>Customized and available in various colors</li>\r\n</ol>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/740081.png', '', '2014-07-18 03:44:43'),
('740325', 'MAGNIFYING WORK LAMP', 'Dental', 'Prosthodontics', 'Accessories', 6.3, '<p>\r\n<b>Features:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>22 Watt compact fluorescent lamp located behind magnifier increases the angle of light\r\nincidence for highlighting object details.\r\n<li>The 5 inch diameter optical magnifier is available in a 3-diopter lens (+75%) or\r\n5-diopter (+125%) lens.\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'images/products/Dental/Prosthodontics/740325.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:39:48'),
