('807800', 'TENS DUAL CHANNEL', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'Equipments', 1.2, '<p>Battery operated, Digital display,\r\n reusable electrodes.</p><p>The Combo unit integrates EMS and TENS functions with 7 treatment modes. This unit is a hybrid stimulator which can be used for muscle stimulation and pain relief.</p><ol><li>Channel	- Dual\r\n<li>Intensity - 0 ~ 80mA\r\n<li>Wave form - Asymmetrical rectangular biphasic pulse.\r\n<li>Power source - DC 9V\r\n<li>Size - 13.6(L)x7(W)x2.65(H)(cm)\r\n<li>Weight - 162 grams (battery included)\r\n<li>Pulse Rate - 2Hz~20 Hz in 1 Hz/step and 20~ 150 Hz in 5 Hz/step.\r\n<li>Pulse Width - 50uS~300uS, 10uS/step.\r\n<li>Output mode - S, A, N, M, B, SD, MR		\r\n<li>Contraction Time - 2~90 seconds	\r\n<li>Relaxation Time - 2~90 seconds	\r\n<li>Ramp Time - 1~8 seconds	\r\n<li>Timer - 5~90 Minutes or continue.\r\n<li>Electrode Detection - Option function, Only active in Pulse Width between from 100uS and 300uS.\r\n<li>Compliance Timer - The patient compliance timer can memorize 100 sets of therapy session records; the total record time is 400 hours; 240 minutes for a single therapy session.\r\n</ol>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/807800.png', '', '2014-07-17 13:02:30'),
('809539', 'X-RAY FILM STORAGE BOX', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'X-Ray-Accessories', 1.7, '<p>Mobile Lead box\r\ncapacity minimum 6 packets\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/809539.png', '', '2014-07-18 03:38:01'),
('810272', 'ADVANCE ROTARY MICROTOME', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Microtomes', 7.1, '<p>\r\nADVANCE ROTARY MICROTOME (LATEST "SPENCER" 820 - \r\nTYPE) : With feed indicators and CAM DRIVE SYSTEM for accurate feed settings from 1-50 microns\r\nin steps of 1 micron each, automatic safety device, universal knife holder with lateral movements \r\nto permit use of complete knife edge, ball &fIange type object holder for accurate centering of the \r\nspecimen, razor 120 mm with back & handle is fabricated from imported fine grain steel alloy  \r\ntested for micro structure and is heat treated to maintain optimum strength and sharpness. </p>\r\n<p>Supplied complete with object holder, dust cover, oil can, honing stone & wooden cabinet.\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/810272.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:40:18'),
('815338', 'FIXATOR TOOL', 'Dental', 'Orthodontics', 'Articulators-and-Accessories', 3.2, '<p> Orthodontic Split Fixator</p><p><b>1. FIELDS OF APPLICATION</b><br /><br />The  Orthodontic Split Fixator is a vertically adjustable occlusion holder with adjustable bite opening forfunctional orthodontics. Two round telescopes prevent rotation in the horizontal axis.</p><p><b>2. ADVANTAGES</b><ol><li> Economical</li><li>Easy handling</li><li>Exact fixation</li><li>Enables simultaneous plastering of upper and lower models</li></ol></p><p>\r\n<b>3. PROCESSING /INSTRUCTIONS</b><br />\r\n<br /> Mounting of models into the fixator Firstly the centring tips are\r\nscrewed\r\ntightly into the fixator arms and the arms are greased. The upper and\r\nlower models, which are waxed together, are fixed between the\r\ncentring tips and the knurled screws\r\nOrthodontic Split Fixator are tightened.Subsequently both model bases can\r\nnow be covered with plaster and the lower model can be set into a prepared\r\nplaster cake. Plaster is applied to the base of the upper model and smoothened\r\nwith the fixator. The exposed areas of the fixator and the screw slits must be\r\ncleaned of plaster before setting.\r\n<br /><br />Removal of models from fixator After complete unscrewing of the\r\ncentring tips the models can be drawn off respectively pushed out from fixator\r\narms without canting. If the models should be put back into\r\nthe Orthodontic Split Fixator the contact areas particularly the ones on\r\nthe plaster model must be thoroughly examined for cleanness. It is important\r\nto allocate the models to the respective fixator parts.\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Orthodontics/815338.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:23:23'),
('815368', 'CAUTERY KIT', 'Dental', 'Periodontics', 'Equipments', 2.1, '<p>The appliance is a diathermic coagulator (radio frequency ESK) designed for use in medical, dental and\r\nveterinary surgeries for minor surgery and micro cauterization for brief\r\nand intermittent interventions (20 seconds max.).The appliance features double electrical insulation (Class II) and a\r\ndedicated system protecting against stray currents and ground faults, with\r\nparticular regard for the ground electrode on the patient (BF type\r\nappliance).The package contains:</p>\r\n<ol><li>power supply unit;\r\n<li>handpiece;\r\n<li>pedal;\r\n<li>cable with neutral cylindrical electrode;\r\n<li>case with n° 8 electrodes;\r\n<li>user instructions.</ol>\r\n<p>The appliance can be transported by hand.</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Periodontics/815368.png', '', '2014-07-18 06:45:59'),
('81604', 'SURVEYOR', 'Dental', 'Prosthodontics', 'Equipments', 6.1, '<p>\r\n<b>Features:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nIncludes survey table, undercut gauge. wax trimmer, carbon markers.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<b>Specifications:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Dimension: W 226 x D 146 x H 287 mm\r\n<li>Weight: 2 kgs\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'images/products/Dental/Prosthodontics/81604.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:31:07'),
