('817230', 'PROJECTION MICROSCOPE', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Microscopes', 7.2, '<p>\r\nPROJECTION MICROSCOPE (with HALOGEN LAMP): (As per\r\nMP-3 Metronex, Warszawa, Lenameter). A highly advanced projection equipment providing\r\nadditional advantage for specimen measurements. Equipped with a Bright Halogen Lamp 195\r\nmm dia, a graduated screen ROTATABLE through 360° and a built in movable compensating \r\neye piece to provide\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Mag. Range : 125X to 1000X with following four objectives alongwith\r\n<li>Objectives : 4 (Nos.)- 5X, 10X, 20X & 40X/45X.\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nComplete with one stage micrometer for measurements & a dust cover\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSENIOR PROJECTION MICROSCOPE (with HALOGEN LAMP) _    \r\nAll specifications as per model MPM-585 but equipped with a latest set of IMPORTED DIN-\r\nSTANDARD TC-SERIES Optics.\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Magnification Range : 10OX to 1500X    \r\n<li>Eye Piece : WF10x(1Pair) \r\n<li>Objectives : 5 Nos-4/5X, 10X, 20X ,45X & 60X \r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nComplete with one stage micrometer for measurements & a dust cover\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nTRINOCULAR PROJECTION MICROSCOPE : Same as MPM-\r\n585A, but supplied with Trinocular Head and pointer arrangement on screen to be used as a\r\nBinocular cum Projection microscope. It comes with latest sets of Imported Din-standard\r\nOptics TC-SERIES\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Magnification Range : 100X to 1500X \r\n<li>Eyepiece : WF 10X(1 Pair)\r\n<li>Objectives ( 5 Nos.) : 4/5X, 10X, 20X, 45X & 60X\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nComplete with one stage micrometer for measurements & a dust cover\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/817230.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:29:49'),
('817535', 'BIOPSY KIT', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'Consumables', 1.6, '<p>\r\n<b>Kit includes:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Curved Scissors\r\n<li>Needle Holder Set\r\n<li>Scissors Set\r\n<li>Tissue Forceps\r\n<li>Sterilisation cassette\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/817535.png', '', '2014-07-18 03:02:38'),
('820800', 'COMPOSITE FILLING INSTRUMENT', 'Dental', 'Endodontics', 'Instruments', 4.2, '<p>The Trimax composite instrument is designed to assist\r\nthe dentist in achieving ideal proximal contact\r\nareas in light cured posterior composite restorations.\r\nIn addition, the optically clear light tip provides increased\r\ncuring ability by allowing efficient light energy\r\ntransmission to the full depth of the restoration. By\r\ncuring in layers and using focused light energy provided\r\nby the specially designed light tip, post-curing\r\nshrinkage is minimized. The optically clear light tips\r\nare essentially micro light guides. They come in three\r\nsizes; premolar, molar and large molar. Size is selected\r\nbased on the size of the preparation. A soft wax\r\nsuch as periphery wax can be utilized to make an\r\nindex of the preparation in order to estimate size.\r\nEach light tip has an annular groove positioned 4mm\r\nabove its tip to guide the dentist in achieving an ideal\r\nmarginal ridge position for each restoration.<br /><br /><b>Features</b></p><ol>\r\n<li>Optically clear tips provide excellent light transmission.\r\n<li>Permits matrix band to be held in contact with \r\nadjacent tooth.\r\n<li>Clear disposable tips come in three different sizes.\r\n<li>Tips have circular ring depth gauge that illuminates \r\nwhen curing light is applied.\r\n<li>Tips are disposable.\r\n<li>Disposable tips can easily be modified.\r\n<li>Tips can be inserted in four positions at right angles to \r\none another.\r\n<li>Triangular ergonomic handle has unique finger rests.<li>  The handle is made of high tech crystal polymer plastic.\r\n<li>Handle incorporates straight and contra-angled ends\r\nmarked by one or two rings.\r\n<li>Hand piece ends have a rest position for light guide.</ol> \r\n<p><b>Benefits</b></p>\r\n<ol><li>Provides improved polymerization and \r\nreduced shrinkage.\r\n<li>Eliminates open contact areas.\r\n<li>Ideal anatomical form for premolar, molar and \r\nlarge molar restorations.\r\n<li>Tip provides guide for proper marginal ridge \r\nheight for improved anatomy.\r\n<li>Enables instrument to easily accept new size \r\nand shape tips, as they become available. \r\nNo degradation in output due to sterilization.\r\n<li>Tips can be used in special situations to create \r\nindividualized designs.\r\n<li>Functions easily to easily work from front or \r\neither side of the mouth.\r\n<li>Easy and comfortable to hold in all positions.\r\n<li>Handle can be safely sterilized with all \r\nmethods in current use.\r\n<li>Each end is designed for ease of use in \r\nmesial and distal positions.\r\n<li>Provides for stable support for light guides in \r\nthe range of 7–11mm diameters.\r\nactual size</ol>', 'images/products/Dental/Endodontics/820800.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:55:17'),
('821075', 'WARP AROUND APRON (Double Sided)', 'Medical', 'X-Ray Apron', '', 0, '<p>Convenience is another name for the <b> Warp Around</b>. Apart from providing all-round protection, it also fits the body comfortably enough to prevent discomfort when worn for longer periods of time.</p>', 'images/products/Medical/X-Ray-Apron/821075.png', '', '2013-12-02 08:24:31'),
('822662', 'MICROWAVE', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Equipments', 7.4, '<p>\r\nMICROWAVE\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/822662.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:46:18'),
('822723', 'PERIOTOME', 'Dental', 'Periodontics', 'Speciality-Instruments', 2.2, '<p>AXE Periotomes are designed for separating the periodontal ligament from the tooth in preparation for a dental implant. After the periodontal ligament is cut and the tooth removed,the underlying bone structure remains intact, providing the necessary foundation for an implant supported replacement tooth. AXE Periotomes are available as  three tips: Straight-Blade, Hatchet-Blade and Hoe-Blade & Handle.</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Periodontics/822723.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:07:41'),
('823425', 'Plate and Screws Kit List 1', 'Dental', 'Oral Surgery', 'Plate and Screws Kit', 0, '<thead><tr><th></th></tr></thead>\r\n<tr><td>TITANIUM PLATES 1.5MM</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 2 holes</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 4 holes</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 4 holes with gap</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates L shape R & L</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates Orbit holes</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 20 Holes </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>TITANIUM PLATES 2MM</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 2 holes</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 4 holes</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 4 holes gap</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates L shape R & L</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>titanium Plates Orbit holes</td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Titanium Plates 20 Holes </td></tr>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Surgery/823425.png', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Surgery/thumbs/823425.png', '2014-07-19 03:37:22'),
('827728', 'SEMI AUTOMATIC MICROTOME', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Microtomes', 7.1, '<p>\r\nSEMI AUTOMATIC MICROTOME is a new generation motorized\r\nMicrotome. In this manual sectioning is enhanced by the high precision motorized specimen feed\r\nwhich provides efficient operation with high repeatability. It comes with an advanced imported\r\ndrive system design on micro step motor and high precision ball screw. LCD screen display set  \r\nparameter like sectioning thickness, retraction value, count of section, travel etc. It has also has\r\nsafety alarm system. It comes with a lockable handwheel at any position. The incorporated storage\r\ntray holds all required subsidiary tools and huge volume waste tray to collect sectioning waste. <br /><br />\r\n<b>Technical Specifications:</b>\r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Section thickness Setting range : 0.5pm-100 pm \r\n<li>Trimming thickness setting range : 1pm-600pm\r\n<li>Setting values : 0.5um-5pm increment step 0.5pm, 5pm-20pm increment step 1 pm, 20pm-60pm increment step 5 pm, 60pm-100pm increment step 10 pm\r\n<li>Minimum setting value : 0.5 pm\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nComplete as above and supplied with sample pack of disposable blades.\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/827728.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:45:49'),
('828460', 'AUTOMATIC SLIDE STAINING MACHINES', 'Dental', 'Oral Pathology', 'Equipments', 7.4, '<p>\r\nAUTOMATIC SLIDE STAINING MACHINE (12 STATIONS) With 3\r\ntwelve staining troughs (one having inlet/outlet) one slide carrier six one \r\nhour calibrated \r\ntiming discs and the plier for programming timing disc etc and a dust cover\r\nMSS-E12: Similar to model MSS-M12, but the instrument is micro-processor based and  \r\noperated through a feather touch keyboard with digital display for adjusting the time      \r\nsequence. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nSupplied with staining troughs 12 nos, slide carriers 1 nos and a dust cover\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAUTOMATIC SLIDE STAINING MACHINE (23 STATIONS) Its \r\ntwo tier arrangement has 11 troughs and a blank station in the upper tier and 12 trough\r\nstations in the lower tier A simple switching system facilities the use of this machine in 3 \r\nmodes: \r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>As one unit utilizing all the 23 staining stations in series.\r\n<li>As two Independent staining machines working at the same time and programmed  \r\nseparately (independent grouping).\r\n<li>As two staining machines operating simultaneously with same time staining cycle ( Parallel \r\nGrouping).\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\nSupplied with Staining Troughs 23 nos, Slide carriers 2 nos, Calibrated Timing Disc 1hr 6 nos, Complete with one plier for programming and dust cover\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nMSS-E23: Similar to model MSS-M23, but the instrument is micro-processor based and \r\noperated through a feather touch keyboard with digital display for adjusting the \r\ntime sequence to use the machine in following style: \r\n</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>As one unit utilizing all the 23 staining stations in series\r\n<li>As two independent staining machine working at the same time and programmed    \r\nseparately (independent grouping)\r\n<li>As two staining machines operating simultaneously with same time staining \r\ncycle (parallel grouping). \r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSupplied with staining troughs 23 nos, slide carriers 2 nos and a dust cover\r\n</p>\r\n', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Pathology/828460.png', '', '2014-07-18 13:57:46'),
('829681', 'X-RAY BITEWING LOOPS', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'Positioning-Devices', 1.5, '<ol><li>Digital Sensor Loops are designed to slip over digital\r\nsensors, providing a handy tab to correctly position sensors for\r\nbitewing radiographs.</li>\r\n<li>Fast and easy — just slides\r\nover bagged sensor</li>\r\n<li>Heavy duty paperboard maintains positioning</li>\r\n <li>Disposable for optimum infection control</li>\r\n <li>More economical than self-adhesive tabs</li>\r\n<li>Minimum separation of maxillary and mandibular teeth</li>\r\n <li>Comfortable for your patient</li>\r\n<li>Easy to use and comfortable</li>\r\n<li>Provides accurate placement of film.</li>\r\n</ol>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/829681.png', '', '2014-07-17 13:25:09'),
('830169', 'FILM SCANNER', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'Scanners-and-Camera', 1.3, '<p>The Advanced Total Film, Document and Photo Scanning Solution for the Professional User</p><ol><li>Advanced Epson Dual Lens System</li>\r\n<li> 6400dpi lm scanning</li>\r\n<li>DIGITAL ICE ™ and DIGITAL ICE Lite™ Technologies</li>\r\n<li>On-board ASIC for dedicated image processing</li>\r\n<li>Optical Density of 4.0 Dmax</li>\r\n<li>Features IEEE1394 (Firewire) and USB 2.0 for high speed scanning for both Windows® and Macintosh® users</li></ol><p>Tailored specifically to meet the high level requirements of scanning\r\nprofessionals, the Epson Perfection V700 Photo incorporates new and refined technologies that work in tandem to provide a fast, total scanning solution with quality rivalling many drum scanners.Dual Lens System Featuring an advanced dual optical lens, the Epson Perfection V700 Photo incorporates two separate lenses, each designed to optimise the scanning results in specific modes. When selecting Film (with Film Holder) mode, the Epson Perfection V700 Photo will 4800dpi High Resolution Lens will be used for reflective scans and film scanning with the Film Area Guide. 4800dpi Matrix CCD The 4800dpi Matrix CCD (Charge Coupled Device) used in the Epson Perfection V700 Photo is one of the crucial factors in the scanner’s ability to scan at incredible detail and deliver high gradation reproduction. It is also the combination of the Matrix CCD with Micro Lens and Epson Dual Lens System that makes it possible for the Epson Perfection V700 Photo to deliver high resolution scans without an increase in carriage size.</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/830169.png', '', '2014-07-17 13:08:55'),
('830902', 'MADAJET', 'Dental', 'Endodontics', 'Equipments', 4.1, '<ol><li> Injects local anesthetics into palataland soft tissues with greater ease and virtually no pain.<li> Provides instant local anesthesia or regional blocking for many dental and Maxillofacial procedures.<li>Excellent patient acceptance for over 25 years.<li>Has interchangeable Extenda Tips for easy sterilization.<li>Can be used with all age groups.<li>Comes with a full year warranty.<li>Provides adequate anesthesia for deepneedle insertion.</ol><p><b>Specifications:</b><br /><br />\r\nConsistent depth of penetration of 2 - 2.5mm below epithelium and makes a\r\nwheal at the base of injection of 5 - 6mm in diameter (Not Topical).\r\nConsistent volume of 0 .1cc per injection intradermally.\r\nPermits approximately 38 injections with single l oading (to 4.0 cc).\r\nMay be sterilized by autoclaving or your usual sterilization process -\r\nDO NOT USE DRY HEAT.<br /><br /><b>Package No. 301 Contains:</b><br /><br />\r\none MadaJet XL, two 1/2"\r\n(127mm) Extenda Tips ®,\r\nholder, wrench, stylets,\r\ntwo extra pyrex fill-chambers,\r\ncustom carrying case and\r\nMadaCide - FD Disinfectant/Cleaner.\r\nAdditional Extenda Tips ® available.\r\n1 1/2" Extenda Ti ps ® available\r\non request.<br /><br /><b>Applications:</b></p>\r\n<ol><li>Extraction or preparation of deciduous teeth.\r\n<li>Curettage and scaling.\r\n<li>Mental and nasal palatine blocks.\r\n<li>Adequate anesthesia prior to deep-needle\r\ninsertion for palatine and infraorbital blocks.\r\n<li>Adequate infiltration for long buccal blocks,\r\nwithout need for further anesthesia.\r\n<li>Mental f oramen blocks via infiltration at\r\nbuccal surface of mandible.\r\n<li>Minor gingevectomies.\r\n<li>Incision and drainage.\r\n<li>Pulp anesthetic infiltration.\r\n<li>Pointing of abscesses.\r\n<li>Copper tube impressions.</ol><p><b>Maxillary Procedures</b></p>\r\n<ol><li>Similarly for posterior superior blocks for upper molars, middle superior blocks of bicuspids\r\nand posterior palatine blocks.</ol>\r\n<p><b>Mandibular Blocks</b></p>\r\n<ol><li>Two injections prior to deep needle insertion for mandibular blocks will eliminate pain\r\nfrom the needle and fluid pressure.</ol>', 'images/products/Dental/Endodontics/830902.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:44:19');
