('905151', 'MODEL PLATFORM', 'Dental', 'Orthodontics', 'Articulators-and-Accessories', 3.2, '<p>Accurately measures articulator-mounted surgical models in three \r\nplanes of space. Vertical, A-P, and transverse movements of the jaw and jaw segments can be accurately quantified. \r\nParallel reference lines are precisely and quickly scribed in all planes. Model Measuring Kits and Extra Blocks are available for SAM®, Single Pin Hanau, and Denar or Two Pin Hanau.	\r\n</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Orthodontics/905151.png', '', '2014-07-18 07:22:53'),
('911590', 'FILM PROCESSOR XP-05', 'Dental', 'Oral Medicine and Radiology', 'Processors', 1.1, '<p>Open-room operation, low noise, simplicity, safety, speed and durability. Wall-mounted design saves space and increases efficiency in the office. Processes more than one piece of film at once, saving valuable time. Accepts one piece of film every 30 seconds in multi-processing mode, with a total processing time of two to eight minutes per film, depending upon the exposure and machine settings. Film sizes of 2cm x 3cm, 3cm x 4cm and 2. 7cm x 5. 4cm may all be developed using the XP-05. Routine maintenance and chemical solution changes are simple and require no special tools.</p>', 'images/products/Dental/Oral-Medicine-and-Radiology/911590.png', '', '2013-12-01 11:03:50'),
